summary: This document is a filing from the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330), listing discovery materials produced to the defense. It is an index of numerous items including police reports, FBI 302s, deposition transcripts, emails, notes, articles, and other records, organized by witness or subject categories (e.g., Juan Alessi, Lisa Rocchio). The document is subject to a protective order.

keyFacts: The document is a detailed index of discovery materials produced to Ghislaine Maxwell's defense team in her criminal case (20 Cr. 330).
The materials span nearly two decades, from 1995 to 2021, and include police reports, FBI interviews (302s), depositions, grand jury transcripts, emails, notes, and articles.
Numerous witnesses and associates are cataloged, with Juan Alessi and David Rodgers having particularly extensive files containing sworn statements, interviews, and grand jury testimony.
The document is subject to a protective order restricting the disclosure of certain information (paragraphs 7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
The index reveals the scale and scope of the investigation, touching on events in Palm Beach and involving multiple law enforcement agencies over many years.
